tldr: The user requested an evaluation of the codebase for database, dashboard,
  and middleware needs. The project now includes a PostgreSQL database for
  questionnaire responses, a simple admin dashboard with login, and CSV export
  functionality, with authentication handled by Next.js middleware.
overview: The user initiated a project to add database capabilities and an admin
  dashboard to a sleep questionnaire application. The initial codebase was
  evaluated, revealing the need for a database to store questionnaire responses,
  an admin dashboard for data access, and an authentication system. A
   model was added to the Prisma schema, along with API
  endpoints for submitting and retrieving data. An admin dashboard was built,
  featuring a login page and a table to display responses with a CSV export
  option. The authentication system was refined from a custom HMAC-signed
  session to a simpler Next.js middleware implementation, which efficiently
  protects admin routes and API endpoints. Comprehensive testing confirmed that
  questionnaire submissions were saved, the admin dashboard was accessible, and
  data could be successfully exported.
